plain_text:
June 24, 1996         [NOT FOR PUBLICATION]

UNITED STATES COURT OF APPEALS
FOR THE FIRST CIRCUIT



No. 95-1502

JOSE QUINONES-PITA,

Petitioner, Appellant,

v.

UNITED STATES OF AMERICA,

Respondent, Appellee.



APPEAL FROM THE UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT

FOR THE DISTRICT OF PUERTO RICO

[Hon. Jose Antonio Fuste, U.S. District Judge]                                                                 



Before

Selya, Cyr, and Lynch,
Circuit Judges.                                                 



Jose Quinones-Pita on brief pro se.                              
Guillermo  Gil,  United States  Attorney,  Jorge  E. Vega-Pacheco,                                                                             
Assistant United  States  Attorney, and  Nelson Perez-Sosa,  Assistant                                                                  
United States Attorney, on brief for appellee.





Per Curiam.   We have reviewed  the parties' briefs  and                           

the  record on appeal.  We affirm essentially for the reasons

stated in the district court's opinion and order, dated March

15, 1995.

Affirmed.
